question_title: Will the community prediction be higher than 26.00% on 2026-02-11 for the Metaculus question "Will the composition of the US Supreme Court change in 2026?"?
summary: Meta-prediction about whether Metaculus CP rises above 26% by Feb 11. Current CP is 25% (dropped from 26%), with 745 forecasters creating a stable median. No retirement news expected, and both Thomas/Alito have hired full clerk complements signaling they plan to stay. While Manifold is higher at 41%, 8 days is too short for significant convergence. The recent downward trend and large forecaster base make crossing the 26% threshold unlikely.

factors.description: CP already dropped from 26% to 25% - recent trend is downward, away from threshold
Large forecaster base (745) makes median very sticky and resistant to movement
No SCOTUS retirement news expected; Thomas/Alito have hired full clerk complements through OT26
Manifold at 41% vs Metaculus 25% - could influence some forecasters upward
Historical base rate of 34% for SCOTUS vacancies is higher than current 25% estimate
